  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the efficacy of local infiltration analgesia as
      compared to 48-hour interscalene block in treating pain after shoulder arthroplasty. The
      investigators hypothesize a reduced pain score and use of supplemental analgesic medication
      during the first three postoperative days using local infiltration analgesia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
